Phylax does not fork or modify SecretFlow; it depends on the published
`secretflow` package (pinned in parties/requirements-secretflow.txt) and invokes
its documented, stable PSI API (SPU `psi_csv` / `psi_df` with the
`ECDH_PSI_3PC` protocol). See parties/common/psi_secretflow.py.

The pure-Python MODP DDH-PSI backend in parties/common/psi.py is original Phylax
code implementing the same Decisional-Diffie-Hellman commutative-encryption
protocol family, used so the demo is reproducible without native wheels.
